<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n05045i"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n05" href="#n05045i">N05 (VI.B.2)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n05all.htm#n05045i"> 45(i)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Dives only kind word</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">There was a rich man who prayed his brothers to attend to Lazarus so that they might &ldquo;not come to this place.&rdquo; That is the only instance, so far as we know, of souls across the river having any sympathy. And I would rather be in hell asking for water than in heaven denying that petition. <small> R.G. Ingersoll, <a name="MOSES" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#MOSES"><cite title="source">Some Mistakes of Moses</cite></a>, (1879) 17</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: The parable of the rich man and Lazarus, also called the Dives (Latin = rich man) and Lazarus, is from Luke 16:19-31. </mm> </dd></dl>
